Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.96,0:00:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the guest list\Nfor the reception?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.40,0:00:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.63,0:00:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a pretty good understanding\Nof where all the guests were
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.23,0:00:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,during the incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.17,0:00:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Was the governor\Nthe gunman's target?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.17,0:00:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All of the guests are VIPs.\NMost of them probably have enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.34,0:00:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, continue checking\Nfor any connections
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.04,0:00:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the guests might have had\Nwith the gunman.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.21,0:00:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The Frankfurt station\Nis in a state of chaos
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.82,0:00:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,over the convention center\Nshooting, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.62,0:00:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.72,0:00:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though we know who the culprit\Nis, we don't know who he was after.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.52,0:00:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? You know\Nwho the culprit is?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.43,0:00:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. He's a dentist from\Nthe redevelopment section of town.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.53,0:00:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,A dentist, huh?\NHow terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.33,0:00:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.77,0:00:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing... I was thinking of going\Nto a dentist after I retire.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.21,0:01:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been busy every day,\Nso I haven't been able to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.88,0:01:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want a crazy dentist.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.32,0:01:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector, right this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.58,0:01:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.82,0:01:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Inspector Visbaugh
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.56,0:01:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Nordrhein-Westfalen\Npolice department.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.78,0:02:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Reinhart Dinger, age 42,\Noccupation, taxi driver...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.42,0:02:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Suspected of killing a passenger\Nin Gunter Forest Park
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.36,0:02:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as the '97 murder of\Na Bilker Investment Bank employee,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.26,0:03:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the '96 Hofgarten murder,\Nthe '95 Rhine Riverside murder...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.33,0:03:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Dinger is wanted for\Nall of these murders
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.84,0:03:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,which occurred near the\NDÃ¼sseldorf metropolitan area.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.07,0:03:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,\NI hereby request that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.78,0:03:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the suspect be moved to\Nthe state of Nordrhein-Westfalen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.62,0:03:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. Are you ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.38,0:03:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.59,0:03:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.89,0:03:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Shall we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.44,0:03:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want\Nsomething to drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.97,0:03:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.81,0:03:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Smoking's not allowed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.15,0:03:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, "Smoking's prohibited\Nin this coach."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.38,0:03:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.72,0:03:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If only you lived the rest of\Nyour life so morally...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.02,0:04:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people have\Ndied at your hands?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.90,0:04:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Counting precious lives\Non your fingers...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.27,0:04:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the ones you killed will\Nnever be able to rest in peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.72,0:04:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my last job.\NI'm retiring tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.95,0:04:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a boring life as a detective,\Nbut it wasn't bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.83,0:04:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I can live peacefully with\Nmy wife and tend to my garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.10,0:04:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how life is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.40,0:04:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to regret destroying\Nthe modest lives of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.24,0:04:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Even people who spit at me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.15,0:05:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The passenger who I let off at\NAdler Street spit at me as he got off.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.18,0:05:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean that you killed him\Njust for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.92,0:05:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Spitting at people is the most pathetic\Nthing you could do as a person,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.93,0:05:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.73,0:05:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The couple that got on at\NGerresheim Station were even worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.83,0:05:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They started having sex\Nin the back of my car.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.10,0:05:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,In the back of my car!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.47,0:05:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So I killed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.41,0:05:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,A young drunk with\Na foul mouth...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.88,0:05:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,A prostitute who tried to pay\Nthe fare with her body...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.15,0:05:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,An old hag with too much makeup who\Nkept insulting everyone around her...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.29,0:05:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,All sorts of people\Ngot into my taxi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.06,0:05:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They were all scum.\NSo I killed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.61,0:05:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Then let me ask you\None more thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.08,0:06:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the murder of the\NBilker Investment Bank employee?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.95,0:06:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,How was he scum?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.62,0:06:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,He worked diligently, he had honest\Nrelationships, he didn't even smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.09,0:06:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That banker\Nloved his family.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.99,0:06:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you killed him,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.92,0:06:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,a corporate bribery scandal\Ninvolving big-business conglomerates,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.36,0:06:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that he was going to blow\Nthe whistle on, remains in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.30,0:06:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.90,0:06:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,left a bad aftertaste. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.44,0:06:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Just look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.41,0:06:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You talk proudly as if you are\Ndelivering holy retribution,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.21,0:06:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're just trying to\Njustify your actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.31,0:06:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That one. .. I had no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.82,0:06:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Did someone ask you\Nto kill him?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.39,0:06:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't tell you that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.30,0:06:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you,\N"Smoking is prohibited."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.24,0:07:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't put a cigarette\Nin your mouth again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.31,0:07:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do,\NI'll kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.58,0:07:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what\Nmade you like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.49,0:07:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I always have been right.\NBut I just got a little push.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.09,0:07:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,On that day...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.13,0:07:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a man walking his dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.80,0:07:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The man kicked the dog\Nfor just for taking a crap.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.21,0:07:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The dog was terrified.\NAll it did was take a crap.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.38,0:07:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I stopped the man.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.83,0:08:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Before I realized what happened,\NI was being subdued by the police.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.17,0:08:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That's when a boy appeared...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.94,0:08:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And the boy told\Nthe police officer,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.11,0:08:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,"It's not his fault.\NThe man with the dog started it."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.02,0:08:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't arrested\Nbecause of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.39,0:08:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I thanked the boy and told him\Nthat I'd give him a ride home.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.60,0:08:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But he said that he didn't\Nhave a home to return to.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.33,0:08:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, he brought out\Nhis sister from the bushes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.87,0:08:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They were twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.91,0:08:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I didn't have a choice,\Nso I took them to my apartment.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.58,0:08:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Strangely, when they took off their\Ncoats, they were both in pajamas.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.78,0:08:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It was as if they had\Nescaped from a hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.79,0:09:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, the boy's head\Nwas wrapped in bandages.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.86,0:09:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That night, we watched\Nthe news after dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.50,0:09:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I complained to myself as I usually do\Nabout how pathetic the world is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.40,0:09:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How pathetic people are...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.01,0:09:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I said that the scum\Nshould all die!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.11,0:09:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And what do you think\Nthat boy told me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.28,0:09:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He said that I was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.98,0:09:31.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He then told me...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.15,0:09:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We don't need people like that.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.89,0:09:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That was when I was liberated.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.53,0:09:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Cut it out! Are you saying that's\Nwhen you started killing people?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.42,0:10:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Good work, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.02,0:10:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.49,0:10:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Your last job went off\Nwithout a hitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.45,0:10:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I just have to\Nclean out my desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.69,0:10:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much for\Nyour long years of service.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.83,0:10:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm kind of relieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.03,0:10:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there are some\Ncold cases, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.01,0:10:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.02,0:10:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He brought his sister.\NThey were twins.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.45,0:10:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They were both in pajamas.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.69,0:10:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It was as if they had\Nescaped from a hospital.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.23,0:10:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Can you remember anything\Nabout that night?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.10,0:10:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Anything will be fine.\NAnything you can remember will do.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.07,0:10:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Your name is Anna.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.07,0:10:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Anna Liebert. isn't that right?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.84,0:11:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Come to think of it, the boy's head\Nwas wrapped in bandages.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.25,0:11:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The twins are\Nnowhere to be found!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.39,0:11:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.29,0:11:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? When did I meet those kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.06,0:11:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.33,0:11:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It was about 11 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.23,0:11:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,W-What did those\Nchildren look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.57,0:11:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they were blond twins\Nwith beautiful faces.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.08,0:11:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be damned...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.19,0:11:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Those twins\Nthat disappeared...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.89,0:11:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The twins who are central to\Nsolving Doctor Tenma's case.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.43,0:11:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This is frustrating.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.67,0:12:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Just thirty hours until\Nmy retirement...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.41,0:12:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,A vampire, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.84,0:12:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. So that's why you\Nkilled thirteen people.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.82,0:12:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't live without\Ndrinking people's blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.09,0:12:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And they have to\Nbe from virgins.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.25,0:12:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. I want to ask you\None more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.22,0:12:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The murder three months ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.86,0:12:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The daughter of a grocer in Frankfurt...\NFrieder Schelling.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.86,0:12:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you drink her blood too?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.70,0:12:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you did indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.97,0:12:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,As you've said,\Nyour victims until now were all girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.14,0:12:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, you thoroughly researched\Nthem before carrying out your attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.81,0:12:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand how much\Nyou need virgin blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.59,0:12:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But. ..Frieder Schelling...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.26,0:12:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,was twenty-one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.16,0:12:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Although she looked as if\Nshe was still in her teens.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.49,0:13:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's not the issue here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.40,0:13:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,She had worked at a cafe on Zeiler\NStreet in Frankfurt since she was 16.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.37,0:13:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The cafe was next to\Na prestigious gymnasium.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.31,0:13:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,She was an idol to the boys\Nwho attended that gymnasium.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.78,0:13:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But she had a child\Nwhen she was 17.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.58,0:13:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,According to rumors, the father was\None of the students from that gymnasium.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.19,0:13:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,After she gave birth,\Nher parents opened a grocery store.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.49,0:13:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The parents of the student\Nwho got her pregnant were rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.00,0:13:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And rumor has it that her parents\Nreceived a lot of money from them
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.50,0:13:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to open the store.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.20,0:13:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You knew about that, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.20,0:13:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, you researched\Nthose other girls so thoroughly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.18,0:13:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you drink blood even if\Nit's not from a virgin?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.91,0:13:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That one...\Nleft a bad aftertaste.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.22,0:13:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you go after her?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.56,0:14:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I met the real thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.99,0:14:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The "real thing"?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.90,0:14:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it when I met him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.86,0:14:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that I was still just a bat\Nthat just flies around vampires.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.37,0:14:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He is none other than\Nthe real thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.34,0:14:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Did that man tell you to do it?\NWho is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.01,0:14:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did you meet?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.91,0:14:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,In a Frankfurt suburb...\NGriesheim...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.82,0:14:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a park there\Nthat's just like any other.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.96,0:14:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}At a sandbox in that park, he wrote\Na woman's name with a tree branch.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.96,0:14:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And I got to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.90,0:14:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.20,0:14:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you. A real vampire.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.28,0:14:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's strange no matter\Nhow you think of it, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.01,0:14:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The murder of Erich Klemperer\Nfour months ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.52,0:15:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You were only receiving orders\Nin Lower Saxony.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.19,0:15:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So why did you go to Frankfurt\Njust for this man?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.09,0:15:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Did the aliens communicate\Nthis to you as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.50,0:15:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Did the aliens suddenly\Nchange their minds
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.90,0:15:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and tell you to go to\NFrankfurt to kill someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.54,0:15:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Or was there\Na different reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.24,0:15:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Klemperer history\Nis pretty suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.41,0:15:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He defected from East Berlin\Nduring the Cold War.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.21,0:15:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,During the past few years,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.62,0:15:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,his food commerce business\Nseems to have done well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.32,0:15:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are rumors that
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.35,0:15:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,he helped smuggle children\Nfrom the East to the West.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.89,0:15:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.29,0:15:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,he sold children from the East to\Nwealthy childless people on the West.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.07,0:15:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't contacted.\NI met him in person.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.41,0:16:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I was really excited.\NI was standing before a real alien.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.11,0:16:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did he land his UFO?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.78,0:16:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,At a park in Griesheim.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.72,0:16:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He spoke the language of the\Ncosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.82,0:16:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So to make it easy for me to understand,\Nhe wrote letters in the sandbox.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.20,0:16:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish you could feel\Nthat excitement I felt then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.88,0:16:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Good work,\NInspector Visbaugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.61,0:16:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.88,0:16:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You're finally counting down the\Nseconds until retirement, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.58,0:16:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You're thinking of this as getting rid\Nof a nuisance, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.89,0:16:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.46,0:16:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So today, we're celebrating the\Nriddance of a nuisance over drinks!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.03,0:16:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I get the feeling the alcohol\Nis going to taste bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.84,0:17:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's that man?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.10,0:17:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.17,0:17:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Dr. Gillen.\NA criminal psychologist.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.14,0:17:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems he's come to see Dinger,\Nthe serial killer taxi driver.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.01,0:17:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Who asked him to?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.58,0:17:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... He said it was for\Na paper or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.52,0:17:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He's an authority in his field,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.32,0:17:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,so it seems he has connections\Nwith important people.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.86,0:17:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,When the passenger got out of the taxi\Nand spit at you, you ran him over.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.10,0:17:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.97,0:17:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I've said this over and over again\Nduring interrogations,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.07,0:17:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but the people I killed\Nwere all unneeded.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.91,0:17:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You just don't understand\Nhow right I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.92,0:17:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,"How right you are"' huh?\NThen can I ask you one thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.19,0:17:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You're always talkative\Nduring interrogations.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.33,0:18:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But when it comes to talking about\NMr. Oberth of Bilker Investment Bank,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.13,0:18:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't seem as forthcoming.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.93,0:18:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,With the other murders,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.73,0:18:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it's been recorded that you express\Nyour reasons for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.14,0:18:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But with the murder of Mr. Oberth,\Nyou've never given a single clear reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.81,0:18:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to talk\Nto you anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.85,0:18:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,How was it, Dr. Gillen?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.22,0:18:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Inspector Visbaugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.29,0:18:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Dinger say anything\Nof scientific interest?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.50,0:18:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Nothing outside of reports\Nuntil now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.97,0:18:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.57,0:18:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, there's something\NI really want to ask that man.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.91,0:18:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to retire today.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.79,0:18:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't feel right unless\NI ask him this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.29,0:19:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think of this from\Nan academic standpoint?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.16,0:19:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If there was\Na monster-like child...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.80,0:19:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and he grew up and revisited a man\Nwho took care of him as a child...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.47,0:19:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,A "monster-like child"?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.01,0:19:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... It's an absurd story.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.58,0:19:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me the story in detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.52,0:19:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What do the two of you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.32,0:19:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I said that I didn't want to talk\Nto that researcher there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.09,0:19:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm still a detective.\NUntil the end of the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.69,0:19:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an interrogation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.99,0:19:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,About the story you told me yesterday,\Nthe one about the twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.93,0:19:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You told me that\Nthe boy liberated you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.14,0:19:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Suppose that child grew up\Nand asked you to do something...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.98,0:19:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.79,0:20:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Well. .. Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.59,0:20:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The murder of Fritz Oberth from\Nthe Bilker Investment Bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.99,0:20:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you do it\Nat someone's request?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.80,0:20:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,A diligent man. An honest man.\NThat's the kind of man Mr. Oberth was.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.54,0:20:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,He's far from what\Nyou would call scum.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.41,0:20:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He was trying to\Nexpose a bribery scandal
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.25,0:20:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,involving a certain\Nfinancial conglomerate.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.02,0:20:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If you call him scum, it would wreck\Nthe reasoning behind your crimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.29,0:20:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.77,0:20:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He and I don't need words.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.64,0:20:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,"He"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.37,0:20:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That bank employee\Nwas probably trash to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.61,0:21:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I'll believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.74,0:21:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.71,0:21:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.68,0:21:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is he?\NIs he the twin you talked about?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.62,0:21:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,When and where\Ndid you meet him?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.35,0:21:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,In Griesheim.\NAt a park in that town.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.23,0:21:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In a Frankfurt suburb...\NGriesheim.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.23,0:21:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}At a park in Griesheim.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.90,0:21:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He wrote a name\Nin the sandbox...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.81,0:21:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn't say a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.81,0:21:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But I understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.04,0:21:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He wanted me to kill the man\Nwhose name he had written.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.51,0:21:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't need words.\NWe understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.92,0:21:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That we don't need this guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.99,0:21:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.26,0:21:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The three people\Nyou interviewed
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.03,0:21:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,were asked by the same person\Nto commit murders?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.87,0:22:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He tried to make the three murders\Nlose their significance
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.64,0:22:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,by incorporating them into three\Ncompletely unrelated multiple homicides.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.84,0:22:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Lose their significance?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.58,0:22:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?\NTell me in detail.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.68,0:22:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Tenma and Nina\Nhave headed to Frankfurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.32,0:22:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.49,0:22:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He's planning something...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.63,0:22:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,in Frankfurt.
